    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Dinner at the Foodies': Purslane and Anxiety'' (June 6):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Dinner at the Foodies': Purslane and Anxiety'' (June 6):</p>
        <p>When did dinner parties become so full of ''shame'' and ''mortification'' for the host, and stop being a way of expressing joy and appreciation for the company? Folks who view cooking for others as a way of expressing their own obsession with status don't cook often enough and may need different friends.</p>
        <p>Patricia Porter  Quakertown, N.J.</p>
      </block>
